Step 1: Identify the relevant current asset components that are considered "quick" (i.e. excluding inventory). They are:
• Cash on Hand = 927447.32  
• Bank Deposits = 71662.08  
• Interest Receivable = 5264.70  
• Accounts Receivable = 248540.09

Step 2: Sum these amounts to get the numerator:
  Numerator = 927447.32 + 71662.08 + 5264.70 + 248540.09  
    = 927447.32 + 71662.08  
      = 999109.40  
    = 999109.40 + 5264.70  
      = 1004374.10  
    = 1004374.10 + 248540.09  
      ≈ 1252914.19

Step 3: The denominator is the Total Current Liabilities from the balance sheet at end:
  Denominator = 3389719.66

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio:
  Quick Ratio = Numerator / Denominator  
    ≈ 1252914.19 / 3389719.66  
    ≈ 0.3697, which rounds to about 0.37

Thus, the final answer is:
